{"cursor":"4654","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nIn television scheduling, a 'hiatus' refers to a break of at least several weeks\nin the normal schedule of broadcast programming. It can occur during a season of\na television program, or can be between television seasons (usually starting in\nJune and ending in August when shooting starts for the next season) which is\ncalled a 'mid-season break'.\n","linknr":152,"url":"Hiatus_(television)","recorded":1362674835,"links":15,"instances":["anime","television"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Television terminology"],"headings":["Planned hiatus","Cancellation","Other reasons for hiatus","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["finale","television"],["pokémon","anime"]],"members":["pokémon","finale"],"related":["Television_scheduling","Broadcast_programming","Television_season","Television_station","Television_program","NBC","Television_network","Episode","Sweeps","Television_advertising","Guest_stars","Finale_(television)","Television_producer","VH1","Pokémon_(anime)","Dennō_Senshi_Porygon","2007–2008_Writers_Guild_of_America_strike","John_Ritter","Madeline_McCann","Charlie_Sheen"]}